ere “our ravenous hold on the world” is a powerful central element.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAmerican poetryy21st century. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  apoetry, literature, fiction, creative writing, contemporary, art, mortality, marriage, relationships, china, memory, love, desolation, grief, pain, suffering, letting go, nature, imagination, potential, creativity, elegy, loss, death, sorrow, fear, heroism, courage, strength, moving forward, longing, lament, yearning, desire, asia, travel.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z978311063851640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226349732423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226349732/original  a978-3-11-063851-6  Urban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019c2016d2019  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles